### Optimize SQLite Serial Inserts

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/orga/performance-trackings.md

Measures the performance improvement for serial inserts into an SQLite database in RXDB. The optimization involves setting the 'synchronous' PRAGMA to 'normal' and utilizing non-transactional writes for small inserts, reducing the time taken for operations like 'serial-inserts-200'.

```javascript
// Example of optimizing SQLite serial inserts
// Before optimization: ~4000s for 200 serial inserts
// After setting 'synchronous' to 'normal': ~2800s
```

