### RxDB Index Field Ordering for Performance

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/nosql-performance-tips.md

Shows how to test and enforce different orderings of fields in a compound index for RxDB queries. The example highlights choosing ['gender', 'age'] over ['age', 'gender'] when data distribution favors prioritizing 'gender' due to its higher selectivity.

```typescript
const query = myCollection
    .findOne({
      selector: {
        age: {
          $gt: 18
        },
        gender: {
          $eq: 'm'
        }
      },
      /**
       * Because the developer knows that 50% of the documents are 'male',
       * but only 20% are below age 18,
       * it makes sense to enforce using the ['gender', 'age'] index to improve performance.
       * This could not be known by the query planer which might have chosen ['age', 'gender'] instead.
       */
      index: ['gender', 'age']
    });

```

