### Creating Custom IndexedDB Indexes

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/slow-indexeddb.md

Demonstrates how to create and use custom indexes in IndexedDB to improve query performance. This involves adding a helper field to documents and creating an index on this field, which can be more efficient than multi-field normal indexes. It also shows how to construct custom key ranges for querying these indexes.

```typescript
// On document insert add the ageIdCustomIndex field.
const idMaxLength = 20; // must be known to craft a custom index
docData.ageIdCustomIndex = docData.age + docData.id.padStart(idMaxLength, ' ');
store.put(docData);
// ...

// normal index
myIndexedDBObjectStore.createIndex(
    'age-index',
    [
        'age',
        'id'
    ]
);

// custom index
myIndexedDBObjectStore.createIndex(
    'age-index-custom',
    [
        'ageIdCustomIndex'
    ]
);

// keyrange for normal index
const range = IDBKeyRange.bound(
    [25, ''],
    [Infinity, Infinity],
    true,
    false
);

// keyrange for custom index
const range = IDBKeyRange.bound(
    // combine both values to a single string
    25 + ''.padStart(idMaxLength, ' '),
    Infinity,
    true,
    false
);
```

