### RxDB: Store Document Data as Attachment (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/nosql-performance-tips.md

This example shows how to store large or infrequently accessed parts of a document's data in RxDB as an attachment. Instead of parsing the entire JSON document every time, RxDB only fetches attachment data when explicitly requested. This improves performance for documents with complex structures where certain fields are not always needed. It involves inserting a document and then adding an attachment to it.

```typescript
const myDocument = await myCollection.insert({/* ... */});
const attachment = await myDocument.putAttachment(
    {
        id: 'otherStuff.json',
        data: createBlob(JSON.stringify({/* ... */}), 'application/json'),
        type: 'application/json'
    }
);
```

